\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 40. O. euphrasiifolia} Desf.,{\i   Fl. Atl. }{\b 2}: 141 (1798). Erect annual; stems 7-20 cm, hairy and glandular. Leaves 1-foliolate; leaflets 10-25 mm, lower ovate, upper linear. Flowers shortly pedicellate, borne singly at each node in congested racemes which elongate after anthesis. Corolla 12-15 mm, yellow, exceeding the calyx. Legume c. 8 mm. Seeds c. 12, 0·5-1 mm, reddish-brown, tuberculate.{\i   Maritime sands. S.E. Spain} ({\i  Cabo de Gata}). Hs. ({\i  N.W. Africa.})
\par

