\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 47. O. mitissima} L., {\i  Sp. Pl.} 717 (1753). Erect or procumbent annual; stems 15-60 cm, somewhat tomentose or nearly glabrous. Leaves 3-foliolate; leaflets 10-20 mm, obovate or elliptical, sometimes caducous, lower bracts 3-foliolate, upper without leaflets, concave and membranous. Flowers shortly pedicellate, borne singly at each node, in a dense terminal raceme. Calyx-tube glabrous, with very prominent white veins, margins of teeth glandular-ciliate. Corolla 10-12 mm, pink, exceeding the calyx. Legume 5-6 mm, ovate. Seeds 2-3, 1·5-2 mm, dark brown, spinulose. {\i  Mediterranean region, Portugal}. Bl Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu.
\par

