\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 49. O. baetica} Clemente,{\i   Ens. Vid} 291 (1807) ({\i  O. salzmanniana} Boiss. & Reuter). Like {\b 48} but less robust; upper leaves and lower bracts 3-foliolate; corolla about equalling the calyx.{\i   Sandy places. S.W. Spain, S. Portugal.} Hs Lu. ({\i  N.W. Africa}.)
