\pard\f0\fs28 Annual, biennial or short-lived perennial herbs. Leaves 3-foliolate; leaflets usually toothed. Flowers in axillary racemes. Calyx-teeth subequal; corolla yellow or white, rarely tinged with blue or violet, deciduous, free from the staminal tube; stamens diadelphous, the filaments not dilated. Legume globose to obovoid, rarely lanceolate-rhomboid, straight, indehiscent or very tardily dehiscent. Seeds 1-2, rarely more.
